The paper investigates the properties of state dynamics in deep recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and their short-term memory abilities. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits of a layered recurrent organization, which is relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the context of Reservoir Computing, which is related to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories.
